@dscoular I believe your issue is subtly different from @fjwillemsen issue. 

Their issue is that they are using Graphene 1.x, but when someone pip installs graphene 1.x it also installs graphql-core 2.0, which is incompatible with graphene 1.x and results in this error.

Your issue is slightly different because you _are_ installing graphene-django 2.0, but it introduces some backwards incompatibilities and your code hasn't been updated yet. Check out the [Upgrading to 2.0 documentation](https://github.com/graphql-python/graphene/blob/master/UPGRADE-v2.0.md#simpler-resolvers), especially the part about simple resolvers. Your resolve arguments will need to change to something like this:

```
 def resolve_install_order(self, info, id, macaddress):
```

