Probably the issue name is confusing. I don't mean to disable flow control completely but temporary because the main issue I see it is inconsistency between different components of openthread:
- not all platforms enable hw flow control by default (only efr32 and nrf);
- border router doesn't enable hw flow control for wpantund;
- pyspinel doesn't enable hw flow control;
- openthread documentation doesn't mention that flow control should be enabled;
- a user doesn't expect flow control to be enabled for CLI application.

The proposal was to disable flow control till above inconsistencies are resolved or to resolve these issues step by step.

