@EivindEklundGoogle   Yes, please provide some more info & context on what sort of problems you're having. You can open a new issue, or post in the google-groups.

Btw, I'm aware of two problems with the Earley parser: one, that it's inconsistent with its choice of derivations. And two, that its performance declines rapidly when there's a lot of ambiguity. We're currently working on fixing both of these issues, on branch `earley_sppf`. 

However, I'm not aware of any issue with the contextual lexer, except that the error reporting isn't as good (but much better now in 0.6.0). If you can provide examples of problematic behavior in LALR with the contextual lexer, please do!
